https://web.archive.org/web/20170226174953im_/http://www.intel.com/content/dam/doc/manual/io-controller-hub-7-hd-audio-ac97-manual.pdf

Next steps for ac97:
- embed raw audio data directly into memory
	- qemu provides an option for adding devices/drives, but this would require
	both recognizing the drive, and loading the appropriate driver to match the I/O that
	qemu expects. it's its own sidequest
	* we can use the linker and embed the audio directly into it.
- figure out what data format ac97 takes, and the ffmpeg command to do so
	* PCM, 16 or 20 bit resolution. let's go with 16

